/**
 * Batched, run-aware execution of a factorized plan's flat prefix (Phase 2 of the unified-architecture plan). The
 * prefix's index nested-loop join runs as a pull-chain of columnar batch stages — one {@code NativeBatch} of up to 1024
 * rows per depth — instead of row-at-a-time cursors: the root pattern fills whole batches, and every deeper pattern
 * probes per input row with two accelerations the row chain lacks. First, LMDB scans deliver quads in index order, so
 * adjacent input rows repeat probe keys constantly; a stage remembers the previous key's matches (bounded buffer) and
 * replays them without touching the store. Second, probes retain their {@code NativeProbe} across rows, amortizing
 * cursor setup. The chain surfaces as a plain {@link RowCursor} so {@link LmdbNativeFactorizedRows} can drive its tail
 * branches (counts, existence probes, enumeration, multiplicity emission) unchanged on top of it.
 */
